BEGIN_PGML
a.  Use mathematical notation to write "[`11.5`] is greater than [`4.2`]".

    [_]{'11.5>4.2'}{15}

a.  Use mathematical notation to write "age is greater than [`20`]".

    [_]{$overage}{15}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
a.  This is "[`\newcommand{\gt}{>}11.5\gt4.2`]".

a.  We can use the word [|age|]* to represent age, and write [`\newcommand{\gt}{>}\text{age}\gt20\text{.}`] Or we could use an abbreviation like [`a`] for age, and write [`\newcommand{\gt}{>}a\gt20\text{.}`] Or we could use [`x`] as a generic variable, and write [`\newcommand{\gt}{>}x\gt20\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

